<BODY>
Sign up for the <b>CIMB Securities Singapore Youth Challenge 2012</b> now to experience the excitement of buying and selling securities including <b>Singapore stocks, structured warrants and Exchange-Traded Funds (ETFs)</b>.<br/><br/>

And the best thing is that you can trade at any places with you <b>Iphone and Android apps!</b><br/><br/>

Most importantly, there are up to <a href='javascript:OpenNormalWindow("gcCIMB/doc/CIMB Securities Singapore Youth Challenge Competition Guidelines Final (For Compliance & Legal) final Prizes.pdf","Prizes","");'>S$30,000 cash prizes</a> available for teams to grab!<br/><br/>

Participants which are under <b>School Category</b> can register <a href=/gcCIMB/cliAcctRegGame.jsp?type=S target=_blank>here</a> with a team of 2-4 students.</br>
Participants which are under <b>Clubs & Societies Category</b> can register <a href=/gcCIMB/cliAcctRegGame.jsp?type=C target=_blank>here</a> with a team of 4 members, including the President of the Club/Society.</br><br/>

Teams will receive a virtual startup capital of <b>S$80,000</b>.<br/>
Click here to enjoy <a href='javascript:OpenNormalWindow("gcCIMB/doc/CIMB Securities Singapore Youth Challenge Competition Guidelines Final (For Compliance & Legal) final Bonus Early.pdf","Bonus","");'>Early Bird Registration Bonus</a> and <a href='javascript:OpenNormalWindow("gcCIMB/doc/CIMB Securities Singapore Youth Challenge Competition Guidelines Final (For Compliance & Legal) final Bonus Investor.pdf","Bonus","");'>CIMB Securities Youth Account Opening Incentive</a> now!<br/><br/>

Trading period: <b>6<sup>th</sup> February 2012 - 24<sup>th</sup> February 2012, 9:00am to 5:00pm. (Singapore Time, Mondays - Fridays)</b><br/><br/>

All participants are invited to witness the launch of the <b>CIMB Securities Youth Challenge 2012</b> and <b>CIMB - SGX Partnership</b>.<br/><br/>

<table>
<tr align=left valign=middle>
<td>Date</td><td>:</td><td>4<sup>th</sup> February 2012 (Saturday), 9:00am to 3:00pm</td>
</tr>
<tr align=left valign=middle>
<td>Venue</td><td>:</td><td>NTU, Lee Kong Chian Lecture Theatre</td>
</tr>
<tr align=left valign=middle>
<td>GOH</td><td>:</td><td>Mr Heng Swee Keat, Minister for Education, EX-Managing Director of MAS</td>
</tr>
</table>
<br/>

<b>The top 5 teams with the <u>highest total net realized value</u> will proceed to the FINAL ROUND!</b><br/><br/>

During the final round, teams will present their respective trading strategies to a panel of judges.<br/>

The final round is in conjunction with the <b>NTU Singapore Financial Conference 2012</b> where distinguished bankers will be invited to give a series of talks.<br/><br/>

<table>
<tr align=left valign=middle>
<td>Date</td><td>:</td><td>29<sup>th</sup> February 2012 (Wednesday), 1:30pm-6:30pm</td>
</tr>
<tr align=left valign=middle>
<td>Venue</td><td>:</td><td>NTUC Income Auditorium, NTUC Centre, 1 Marina Boulevard NTUC Auditorium, Level 7.</td>
</tr>
<tr align=left valign=top>
<td>Agenda</td><td>:</td><td>
	<table>
	<tr align=left valign=middle>
	<td>1.</td><td>Witness the final round of presentations by top five (5) teams.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr align=left valign=middle>
	<td>2.</td><td>Ask questions on the trading strategies of the top five (5) teams.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr align=left valign=middle>
	<td>3.</td><td>Receive exclusive door gifts</td>
	</tr>
	<tr align=left valign=middle>
	<td>4.</td><td>Listen and get insights from a panel of experienced bankers and industry practitioners.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr align=left valign=middle>
	<td>*</td><td>Refreshment are provided</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<br/>

Teams can find out more information on the competition from the <a href='javascript:OpenNormalWindow("gcCIMB/doc/CIMB Securities Singapore Youth Challenge Competition Guidelines Final (For Compliance & Legal) final.pdf","CompGui","");'>Competition Guidelines</a>.

